| Switched ETM | 0.01 | 80 h | 183 |

(Other simulation tables — Tables 3–5 — show restricted relationships between $F_{\min}$ and $F_{\max}$ and decay rates for different interval sizes.)

---

## 5 Conclusion

This paper investigated event-triggered control of CPSs under deception attacks. A queuing model was constructed to depict deception attacks. A switched event-based communication scheme was proposed to adapt triggering according to attack mode and save network resources. Using piecewise Lyapunov functionals, fuzzy controllers and ETM parameters were co-designed to guarantee exponential stability. The approach was validated on a mass–spring–damper example. Future work includes extending the method to CPSs with exogenous disturbances and more general cyber-attacks.

